text: The nasi briyani mutton is a must to try. Mutton is juicy and tender.
Enjoyed the fish soup here a lot, cheap and the soup broth is really flavorsome (yet not murky), they do a good bowl of dry ban mian. All $3.50-$4... cheap and good!
The food here is nice and cheap. But don't ever park at the parallel season lots. The wilson attendant is very on. Once your vehicle is clamped, u need to pay $108 to release. Don't try your luck

The best malay dishes or food i have ever had !! Their briyani rice is highly pleasant to the taste.. Their ayam penyet is very delicious moreover the sambal just kicks in with rich and savoury taste ! Nasi ambeng is also the best ! Appetizing only by look but what more when u try and taste it on ur own :)
No words can describe how enjoyable, inviting & finger-licking their food are !
